font-size:11pt">.  </span></li></ol></ol><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ol start="5" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.63pt; padding-left:5.37pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">PHE recognises that there are instances whe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">re women feel that they have not been able to progress their careers due to factors that have already been identified</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> within</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> other organisations and scientific environments, e.g. </span></li><ol type="i" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Caring responsibilities, in particular caring for young children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which ofte</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n coincide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> with the period when </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women scientists</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> should be consolidating and building their careers and maintaining their publication record.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:14pt; mar